Electron-glow is electron with added functions that makes it possible to
interact with the PiGlow devLib of the wiringPi library by Gordon Henderson.

What does this do? Makes it possible to control the LEDs of the Pimoroni
PiGlow! Use cmd/electron-glow.clp as a wrapper library over the raw commands
exposed by electron.

NOTE: You need to have a raspberry pi to have this work!

wiringPi can be acquired at https://projects.drogon.net/ and is licensed under
the GNU LGPL v3.
